{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566995","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566995"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18915"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18915"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.01,0.93,0.03,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11648"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80181"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11648","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11648"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18915"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65458"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"11361"},{"type":"tags","id":"11362"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27398"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27399"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45084"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80181","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80181"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 14-year-old presents to the clinic requesting contraceptive advice. The young person asks that their parents not be informed of the consultation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate approach to assessing this young person\u0027s capacity to consent?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Defer all decisions until age 16","Automatically refer all decisions to the parents","Assess understanding of treatment benefits and risks","Require parental consent due to age alone","Proceed without any capacity assessment"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eassess understanding of treatment benefits and risks\u003C/strong\u003E. This aligns with the principle of Gillick competence, which recognises that minors under 16 may have capacity to consent to medical treatment if they demonstrate sufficient maturity and intelligence to understand the nature and implications of the treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAutomatically refer all decisions to the parents\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to respect the young person\u0027s developing autonomy and right to confidential healthcare if deemed competent\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequire parental consent due to age alone\u003C/strong\u003E - Age alone does not determine capacity; each case must be assessed individually based on the young person\u0027s understanding\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefer all decisions until age 16\u003C/strong\u003E - This arbitrary approach ignores that some young people may be competent to make decisions before age 16\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProceed without any capacity assessment\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to ensure the young person has sufficient understanding to make an informed decision\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers must carefully assess the young person\u0027s understanding of the proposed treatment, its benefits, risks, and alternatives. This includes their ability to weigh information and make a voluntary decision. If deemed competent, the young person\u0027s right to confidentiality should be respected unless there are serious safeguarding concerns.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gillick competence determines if children under 16 can consent to medical treatment based on their maturity and understanding.","Healthcare providers must assess a child\u0027s capacity to understand treatment implications before obtaining consent.","Parents retain responsibility for medical decisions when children lack capacity to consent."],"references":["Griffith R. What is Gillick competence? Hum Vaccin Immunother. 2016;12(1):244-7. doi: 10.1080/21645515.2015.1091548. PMID: 26619366; PMCID: PMC4962726. Avaialble from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26619366/","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65458"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18915"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65458","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65458"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T07:17:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T07:18:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11648"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80181"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5